WLJS Notebook Demonstration Project

Here is a compilation of various notebooks showcasing examples of how to use the Wolfram Language and the dynamic features of our frontend, posted as static web pages. You can create your own page like this using the `Share` feature.

Each example can be reopened in the app as a regular notebook by clicking on the question mark in the top-right corner.

*Boids animation by VANTA.js project*

Useful links

- [Documentation](https://jerryi.github.io/wljs-docs/)

- [Releases](https://github.com/JerryI/wolfram-js-frontend/releases)

- [Github discussions](https://github.com/JerryI/wolfram-js-frontend/discussions)

WLJS Notebook is an open-source notebook interface created for a freeware implementation and a standard library of Wolfram Language - Wolfram Engine

Data visualization

Some examples on the data visualization using Woflram Language. Note that examples below do not cover even `10%` of the standard library. Please see the reference section in our documentation.

- [`Plot`](/wljs-demo/plot.html) standard `Plot` function

- [`Plot3D`](/wljs-demo/plot3d.html) family

- [`Plotly`](/wljs-demo/plotly.html) an adaptation of a well-known `Plotly` library used in Javascript, Python and R

- [`Histogram`](/wljs-demo/histogram.html) examples with histograms

- [`Graphs`](/wljs-demo/graphs.html) demo of a standard library for building and computing using graphs

- [`Dataset`](/wljs-demo/dataset.html) a dataset structure for representing and manipulating the data

- [Lights and shadows](/wljs-demo/shadows_and_light.html) Plotting Hundreds of Polygons Using the Power of WebGL

- *many more*

Here is some ==interactive examples== on dynamic evaluation. **Try to drag sliders on a web-page**

- [Quantum Well](/wljs-demo/quantum_well.html) a numberical solution for Schrodinger equation in a case of 1D confinment.

- [Manipulate Plot](/wljs-demo/manipulate_plot.html) a basic example on a live data manipulation

- [Maxwell FDTD](/wljs-demo/maxwell_fdtd.html) a numerical solution 1D wave propagating through a thin plate

- [`AnimatePlot`](/wljs-demo/animation.html) simple backed animations for 2D plotting

- [Basic dynamic evaluation 1](/wljs-demo/orb.html)
